a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D37332", "files": ["gfx/vr/VRManager.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d9f505410a6b79f45d05387507b9f64de9b32658", "parents": ["e9f698a366687d1242bb6d9bda1133c81ea19f6c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Marco Bonardo \u003cmbonardo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1552141 - The address bar is filtering bookmarklets and not executing them. r=dao a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D37218", "files": ["browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarInput.jsm", "browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarProviderUnifiedComplete.jsm", "browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarProvidersManager.jsm", "browser/components/urlbar/tests/browser/browser_keywordBookmarklets.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2c36222570a9ffb0d1209faa92281365b1bd4fa2", "parents": ["d9f505410a6b79f45d05387507b9f64de9b32658"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alastor Wu \u003calwu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1305732 - part1 : don't show the box with zero width or height. r=heycam a=RyanVM\n\nSetting cue's position would also affect cue box's size which would be determined by cue's position alignment as well. If the cue box's width or height is zero, it means that this box should not be display on the screen and we should clear cue's display state as well.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D35693", "files": ["dom/media/webvtt/vtt.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ebd13e20a8728c22db39162c0a93bb6dcd07454c", "parents": ["2c36222570a9ffb0d1209faa92281365b1bd4fa2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "alwu \u003calwu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1305732 - part2 : list all properties set on the root node in one place to make them clear. r=heycam a=RyanVM\n\nIn order to clearly see what properties are applied on the root node, create a function to list all of them together.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D36847", "files": ["dom/media/webvtt/vtt.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bfa35429419f4f8b28adef941b5e67f78ae3fc98", "parents": ["ebd13e20a8728c22db39162c0a93bb6dcd07454c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "alwu \u003calwu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1305732 - part3 : remove redundent properties setting on non-pseudo background node. r=heycam a=RyanVM\n\nIf the background node is not a pseudo element, these properties would actually be inherited, so we have no need to set them again.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D36848", "files": ["dom/media/webvtt/vtt.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0e4e5645b8223acdab08e9450291b6d512e55c64", "parents": ["bfa35429419f4f8b28adef941b5e67f78ae3fc98"], "tags": []}, {"author": "alwu \u003calwu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1305732 - part4 : background box should be a inline node. r=heycam a=RyanVM\n\nAccording to the spec [1], the background box should be `display:inline`.\n\nTherefore, we should create a `\u003cspan\u003e`, which already is an inline element, for the background box, not a `\u003cdiv\u003e`, which is a block element.\n\nIn addition, when the pseudo element is enabled, even though the element is currently a `div`, it doesn't match the div `{ display: block; }` rule from the UA style sheet because the pseudo element only matches `::cue` rules. It also has the initial value of display which is `inline`.\n\n[1] https://www.w3.org/TR/webvtt1/#webvtt-cue-background-box\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D36849", "files": ["dom/media/webvtt/vtt.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cb42f7e76d0fed643773da7644f7bb476266dc26", "parents": ["0e4e5645b8223acdab08e9450291b6d512e55c64"], "tags": []}, {"author": "alwu \u003calwu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1305732 - part5 : set CSS properties directly on '::cue'. r=heycam,emilio a=RyanVM\n\nAccording to the spec [1], we have to set those CSS properties on the root node, and then this root node would have a child node, background box [2], which would contain all other child nodes.\n\nIn our case, the background box is `cueDiv` [3].\n\nIn theory, all those properties set on the root node should be inherited by the background box. However, when the background box is a pseudo element `::cue`, they won't be directly inherit from the the background box's parent, inherited styles would acutally come from video instead.\n\nTherefore, we have to directly set these properties on the pseudo element and mark them as `!important` to avoid being overrided by user style script.\n\n[1] https://www.w3.org/TR/webvtt1/#ref-for-list-of-webvtt-node-objects-9\n[2] https://www.w3.org/TR/webvtt1/#webvtt-cue-background-box\n[3] https://searchfox.org/mozilla-central/rev/11712bd3ce7454923e5931fa92eaf9c01ef35a0a/dom/media/webvtt/vtt.jsm#533-534\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D35694", "files": ["dom/media/webvtt/vtt.jsm", "layout/style/res/html.css", "servo/components/style/properties/longhands/inherited_box.mako.rs", "servo/components/style/properties/longhands/inherited_text.mako.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8c74a8452ad56f63645f70ca737598dbc007b0bf", "parents": ["cb42f7e76d0fed643773da7644f7bb476266dc26"], "tags": []}, {"author": "alwu \u003calwu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1305732 - part6 : modify wpts. r=heycam a=RyanVM\n\nIn this patch, we do the following changes.\n\n1. using Ahem and using it as recommanded font size and line height.\n2. reduce the cue text length in `align_center_position_lt_50.vtt` and `align_center_position_gt_50.vtt` in order to prevent text wrapping to multiple lines\n3. wrapping to mulitple lines would be tested in `align_center_position_lt_50_size_gt_maximum_size.html` and `align_center_position_gt_50_size_gt_maximum_size-ref.html`\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D35695", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/webvtt/rendering/cues-with-video/processing-model/align_center_position_gt_50_size_gt_maximum_size.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/tests/webvtt/rendering/cues-with-video/processing-model/align_center_position_gt_50-ref.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/webvtt/rendering/cues-with-video/processing-model/align_center_position_gt_50.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/webvtt/rendering/cues-with-video/processing-model/align_center_position_gt_50_size_gt_maximum_size-ref.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/webvtt/rendering/cues-with-video/processing-model/align_center_position_gt_50_size_gt_maximum_size.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/webvtt/rendering/cues-with-video/processing-model/align_center_position_lt_50-ref.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/webvtt/rendering/cues-with-video/processing-model/align_center_position_lt_50.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/webvtt/rendering/cues-with-video/processing-model/align_center_position_lt_50_size_gt_maximum_size-ref.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/webvtt/rendering/cues-with-video/processing-model/align_center_position_lt_50_size_gt_maximum_size.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/webvtt/rendering/cues-with-video/processing-model/support/align_center_position_gt_50.vtt", "testing/web-platform/tests/webvtt/rendering/cues-with-video/processing-model/support/align_center_position_gt_50_size_gt_maximum_size.vtt", "testing/web-platform/tests/webvtt/rendering/cues-with-video/processing-model/support/align_center_position_lt_50.vtt"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b399656312da76da5a28661dd229b37c0f154b35", "parents": ["8c74a8452ad56f63645f70ca737598dbc007b0bf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "alwu \u003calwu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1305732 - part7 : remove duplicated declaration. r=heycam a=RyanVM\n\nWe have declared `supportPseudo`, remove the duplicated declaration.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D36851", "files": ["dom/media/webvtt/vtt.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "58db79efd8d4923173a9fad2b00e0826712b69de", "parents": ["b399656312da76da5a28661dd229b37c0f154b35"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alastor Wu \u003calwu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1544455 - part1 : check the base direction of cue text in 'ComputedPositionAlign()'. r=heycam a=RyanVM\n\nAccording to the spec [1], when text alignment is `start` or `end`, we have to check the base direction of the cue text in order to decide the position alignment.\n\n[1] https://www.w3.org/TR/webvtt1/#cue-computed-position-alignment\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D35270", "files": ["dom/media/TextTrackCue.cpp", "dom/media/TextTrackCue.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2bd470454f7214f71fc90f4095c9ee58b7f09525", "parents": ["58db79efd8d4923173a9fad2b00e0826712b69de"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alastor Wu \u003calwu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1544455 - part2 : modify test 'test_webvtt_positionalign.html'. r=heycam a=RyanVM\n\nAdd new test cases for alignment `start` and `end` for both LTR and RTL text.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D35271", "files": ["dom/media/test/test_webvtt_positionalign.html", "dom/media/test/vttPositionAlign.vtt"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "66e1967c3c5f58e29401c83598404ead4444a0eb", "parents": ["2bd470454f7214f71fc90f4095c9ee58b7f09525"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alastor Wu \u003calwu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1544455 - part3 : consider the result of computed position alignment to return correct computed position. r=heycam a=RyanVM\n\nIn the spec [1], it only considers text's alignment when computing the `position`. However, the text alignment `start` and `end` can make the same result of what `left` and `right` make, depending on what direction the text uses.\n\nFor example, setting text alignment `left` is equal to `start` for the LTR text. Therefore, we could check the result of `ComputedPositionAlign`, which would return correctly direction automatically accoding to the text's base direction.\n\n[1] https://www.w3.org/TR/webvtt1/#cue-computed-position\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D35272", "files": ["dom/media/TextTrackCue.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "66c851b1788288a0e0553728651e34a4a6cddffe", "parents": ["66e1967c3c5f58e29401c83598404ead4444a0eb"], "tags": []}], "date": 1562845418, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "shindli@mozilla.com"}, "11557": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\naz -\u003e bd126946a150\nfr -\u003e 2819ff8b744a\nhsb -\u003e ece3e75b8d14\nsl -\u003e 3632004fe80c\nsv-SE -\u003e b3810bbfa475\nvi -\u003e 35779e75e0db\nzh-TW -\u003e fdb9f6038bb6", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1006d36821c2ba45924992e0e0b22fa5e792be15", "parents": ["66c851b1788288a0e0553728651e34a4a6cddffe"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\naz -\u003e bd126946a150\nfr -\u003e 2819ff8b744a\nhsb -\u003e ece3e75b8d14\nsl -\u003e 3632004fe80c\nsv-SE -\u003e b3810bbfa475\nvi -\u003e 35779e75e0db\nzh-TW -\u003e fdb9f6038bb6", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "045afc7d3c5728dca55d5499678911fa185c43dc", "parents": ["1006d36821c2ba45924992e0e0b22fa5e792be15"], "tags": []}], "date": 1562850033, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "11558": {"changesets": [{"author": "Sebastian Hengst \u003carchaeopteryx@coole-files.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset ab9d5eeaa90e (bug 1370630) on request from smaug for causing bug 1556980. a=backout", "files": ["dom/events/test/mochitest.ini", "dom/events/test/test_submitevent_on_form.html", "dom/html/HTMLFormElement.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2e181acc2824c0b681f227ceae15bff0c0af4e49", "parents": ["045afc7d3c5728dca55d5499678911fa185c43dc"], "tags": []}], "date": 1562851353, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "11559": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mihai Alexandru Michis \u003cmalexandru@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 2c36222570a9 (bug 1552141) for causing bc failures in browser_keywordBookmarklets.js a=backout", "files": ["browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarInput.jsm", "browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarProviderUnifiedComplete.jsm", "browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarProvidersManager.jsm", "browser/components/urlbar/tests/browser/browser_keywordBookmarklets.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ed2ad6dc85a7a2d1b631cefa577acc0232c4ea0f", "parents": ["2e181acc2824c0b681f227ceae15bff0c0af4e49"], "tags": []}], "date": 1562860678, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "malexandru@mozilla.com"}, "11560": {"changesets": [{"author": "Hiroyuki Ikezoe \u003chikezoe.birchill@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1556275 - Handle unknown values for width and height as 'Auto' in viewport meta tag. r=botond, a=RyanVM\n\nWithout the change a green rectangle in each reftest in this commit covers whole\nscreen.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D37328", "files": ["dom/base/Document.cpp", "layout/reftests/meta-viewport/device-height-for-width.html", "layout/reftests/meta-viewport/invalid-width-ref.html", "layout/reftests/meta-viewport/invalid-width.html", "layout/reftests/meta-viewport/reftest.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f3bf02fa090afdc0dc3ff1e248deb2bb3cf036b7", "parents": ["ed2ad6dc85a7a2d1b631cefa577acc0232c4ea0f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Conley \u003cmconley@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1560590 - Add Telemetry event probes to determine if users tend to move or resize the Picture-in-Picture window after opening it. data-review=chutten, r=JSON_voorhees, a=RyanVM\n\nDepends on D36359\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D36360", "files": ["toolkit/components/pictureinpicture/PictureInPicture.jsm", "toolkit/components/pictureinpicture/content/player.js", "toolkit/components/telemetry/Events.yaml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d2d91301a2a067f99f2f6c076d148535c100d0d1", "parents": ["f3bf02fa090afdc0dc3ff1e248deb2bb3cf036b7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Karan Sapolia \u003csapoliakaran@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1562903 - Fix adding a search engine from a web page on android. r=Standard8, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D37456", "files": ["mobile/android/chrome/content/browser.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2feaf4d8ac53456dcb99457defc9689a0a12fb3e", "parents": ["d2d91301a2a067f99f2f6c076d148535c100d0d1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ehsan Akhgari \u003cehsan@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1558503 - Preserve the order of the arguments in the localized storageAccess.message string; r=johannh,flod, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D37468", "files": ["browser/modules/PermissionUI.jsm", "toolkit/modules/PopupNotifications.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3bcc11455906bcf3bf15037a43ae2007a343c5ac", "parents": ["2feaf4d8ac53456dcb99457defc9689a0a12fb3e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1564078 - Fix use of invocation kind that was previously lost and refactor malloc threshold updates. r=sfink, a=RyanVM\n\nThis restores the use of GC invocation kind that was inadvertantly removed by the patch in bug 1395509 comment 33 from the call to ZoneAllocator::updateAllGCThresholds in GCRuntime::endSweepingSweepGroup.  Also refactors ZoneMallocThreshold::computeZoneTriggerBytes a little.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D36924", "files": ["js/src/gc/GC.cpp", "js/src/gc/Scheduling.h", "js/src/gc/Zone.cpp", "js/src/gc/ZoneAllocator.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1bb8756f2af0a06ed91d111b004237f5089822d7", "parents": ["3bcc11455906bcf3bf15037a43ae2007a343c5ac"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Beich \u003cjbeich@FreeBSD.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1562497 - Build PuppetSession on Tier3 as VRService depends on it. r=daoshengmu, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D36811", "files": ["gfx/vr/service/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "88399471e55995bc768985ade0a507494d09115d", "parents": ["1bb8756f2af0a06ed91d111b004237f5089822d7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "John Lin \u003cjolin@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1563734 - always sync session ID from remote decoder. r=jya, a=RyanVM\n\nIn bug 1552607/D36382, RemoteDataDecoder always increases session ID but\nCodecProxy only performs flush IPC when neccessary. This will cause the\nID numbers out of sync and prevent remote decoder from receiving any\nmore input. By reading the session ID in dequeued input samples, the\nnumbers can always be in sync.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D37123", "files": ["dom/media/platforms/android/RemoteDataDecoder.cpp", "dom/media/platforms/android/RemoteDataDecoder.h", "media/webrtc/signaling/src/media-conduit/WebrtcMediaCodecVP8VideoCodec.cpp", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/gecko/media/Codec.java", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/gecko/media/CodecProxy.java", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/gecko/media/Sample.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0b6b434c5303fa3683d013562be0f727c35cc22f", "parents": ["88399471e55995bc768985ade0a507494d09115d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1562872097, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "11561": {"changesets": [{"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1550023 - Allow WR on a subset of Intel to ride into early beta on Windows. r=jrmuizel a=RyanVM\n\nThis uses positive-but-empty #if conditions with else clauses rather than\ninverted conditions for better readability and documentation.\n", "files": ["gfx/thebes/gfxPlatform.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ebb122d3a9039666139745370d309f4b7739c098", "parents": ["0b6b434c5303fa3683d013562be0f727c35cc22f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1550023 - Move variable into function. r=jrmuizel a=RyanVM\n\nIt doesn't need to be an argument since it's not used by the caller.\n", "files": ["gfx/thebes/gfxPlatform.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1079a6582a0687c1b8457e9ab1417de11cd557aa", "parents": ["ebb122d3a9039666139745370d309f4b7739c098"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1550023 - Qualify whitelisted Intel cards up to WUXGA screen size for Windows in release 69. r=jrmuizel a=RyanVM\n", "files": ["gfx/thebes/gfxPlatform.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c69f2d22e51ef9131843e2806ff20aa16a0de2f8", "parents": ["1079a6582a0687c1b8457e9ab1417de11cd557aa"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1550023 - Don't allow the qualified pref to disable WR for already released populations. r=jrmuizel a=RyanVM\n", "files": ["gfx/thebes/gfxPlatform.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ea96619eb18345b62d6280e61f877bc358af1c91", "parents": ["c69f2d22e51ef9131843e2806ff20aa16a0de2f8"], "tags": []}], "date": 1562872532, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "kgupta@mozilla.com"}, "11562": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\ncs -\u003e 1290cb9a912e\nen-CA -\u003e 5311806492a9\net -\u003e 13ebc05bf7ce\ngu-IN -\u003e dba04d44b0ee\nhsb -\u003e 4806db09d804\nhu -\u003e b92f8a62a3b4\npt-BR -\u003e 39f62a5998e1\nsl -\u003e 29e47ad73793\nsv-SE -\u003e 8255a98dc979\nth -\u003e 1db0a2ad6776\ntr -\u003e 8b4af72aec83\nvi -\u003e c9b99544ac5e\nzh-CN -\u003e b0c9cdf239d3\nzh-TW -\u003e 1a9b37709bd6", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "676c09f04f1182b40a829bcaaefe09e9f7040f44", "parents": ["ea96619eb18345b62d6280e61f877bc358af1c91"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\ncs -\u003e 1290cb9a912e\nen-CA -\u003e 5311806492a9\net -\u003e 13ebc05bf7ce\ngu-IN -\u003e dba04d44b0ee\nhsb -\u003e 4806db09d804\nhu -\u003e b92f8a62a3b4\npt-BR -\u003e 39f62a5998e1\nsl -\u003e 29e47ad73793\nsv-SE -\u003e 8255a98dc979\nth -\u003e 1db0a2ad6776\ntr -\u003e 8b4af72aec83\nvi -\u003e c9b99544ac5e\nzh-CN -\u003e b0c9cdf239d3\nzh-TW -\u003e 1a9b37709bd6", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "48d8c32ddfcfcc365a82891e795b95a3a71971b5", "parents": ["676c09f04f1182b40a829bcaaefe09e9f7040f44"], "tags": []}], "date": 1562875238, "git_changesets"