uyen \u003cntim.bugs@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1565921 - Load editMenuOverlay.js and globalOverlay.js on documents with HTML inputs. r=Gijs a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38018", "files": ["security/manager/pki/resources/content/changepassword.xul", "security/manager/pki/resources/content/exceptionDialog.xul", "security/manager/pki/resources/content/setp12password.xul", "toolkit/profile/content/createProfileWizard.xul"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "98b8c0f975bc22a2929613b1911a2449d20486fc", "parents": ["dab6b5b992787c1265b6ae8337e7bc5db36761fc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luca Greco \u003clgreco@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1556757 - Abuse Report panel should not show the 'broken reason' suggestion when addon support url is missing. r=mstriemer a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D35674", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/abuse-report-panel.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_html_abuse_report.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a706b0b753164bdfa8b8fb59a439842cc440ac9a", "parents": ["98b8c0f975bc22a2929613b1911a2449d20486fc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luca Greco \u003clgreco@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1556403 - Hide abuse report author container element when addon author metadata is not available. r=mstriemer a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D35669", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/abuse-report-panel.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_html_abuse_report.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fc1466c9dd1d8bc09ec41dac7affa1754ad4d402", "parents": ["a706b0b753164bdfa8b8fb59a439842cc440ac9a"], "tags": []}], "date": 1563366415, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "malexandru@mozilla.com"}, "11596": {"changesets": [{"author": "Joel Maher \u003cjmaher@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1563860 - annotate wpt manifest to support both 10.14 and 10.14.5. r=egao, a=test-only\n\nannotate wpt manifest to support both 10.14 and 10.14.5\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D37728", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/html/semantics/embedded-content/the-iframe-element/iframe_sandbox_navigation_download_block_downloads_without_user_activation.sub.tentative.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "de4b6c35ab763aecfd79a67ef090ac558875cd57", "parents": ["fc1466c9dd1d8bc09ec41dac7affa1754ad4d402"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Byron Campen [:bwc] \u003cdocfaraday@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1559512: Make sure that we grab the first RTP packet when checking RTP extensions, because the mid extension is only used in the first several. r=jib, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D37884", "files": ["dom/media/tests/mochitest/test_peerConnection_basicAudioVerifyRtpHeaderExtensions.html", "dom/media/tests/mochitest/test_peerConnection_basicVideoVerifyRtpHeaderExtensions.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d373c9bd50a4f9f34fdd0be5ad709c26fb461fb5", "parents": ["de4b6c35ab763aecfd79a67ef090ac558875cd57"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1562351 - Do the scrollbar drag in one shot to avoid intermittent failures. r=botond, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D37981", "files": ["gfx/layers/apz/test/mochitest/helper_drag_root_scrollbar.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ff3594ae3fe2a4b43791db7e5a921938db50cfbb", "parents": ["d373c9bd50a4f9f34fdd0be5ad709c26fb461fb5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1563541 - Force a paint before reading the APZ test data. r=botond, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D37983", "files": ["gfx/layers/apz/test/mochitest/test_bug1253683.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f0bf36453203427955a6eb92809153f199d099b9", "parents": ["ff3594ae3fe2a4b43791db7e5a921938db50cfbb"], "tags": []}], "date": 1563366951, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "11597": {"changesets": [{"author": "Lee Salzman \u003clsalzman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1553228 - Don't free result of FcPatternGetString. r=jfkthame a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38157", "files": ["gfx/thebes/gfxFcPlatformFontList.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dae4d7fb4d89febb9d67def7c11dcf0a1690a69b", "parents": ["f0bf36453203427955a6eb92809153f199d099b9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matt Howell \u003cmhowell@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1563565 - Raise the stub installer maximum download size limit. r=agashlin a=RyanVM\n\nThe installer for aarch64 Windows has exceeded the current limit. This new one\n(150 MB) should allow enough breathing room while still being reasonable.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38246", "files": ["browser/installer/windows/nsis/stub.nsi"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "40cbf62e4643f4fccf08d7927f527856e5a328c6", "parents": ["dae4d7fb4d89febb9d67def7c11dcf0a1690a69b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicolas Silva \u003cnsilva@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1559688 - Clip tile dirty rects to the tile's total rect. r=aosmond a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D37841", "files": ["gfx/wr/webrender/src/resource_cache.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fad0fd0fe971eed5eeb0f33bb96a0e7960e5c00e", "parents": ["40cbf62e4643f4fccf08d7927f527856e5a328c6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1546027 - Don't apply scroll anchor adjustments if we're restoring our scroll position. r=dholbert a=RyanVM\n\nSince scroll position restoration is absolute, and we'll lose it as soon as we\napply any adjustment or do any other sort of scrolling.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D37941", "files": ["layout/generic/ScrollAnchorContainer.cpp", "layout/generic/nsGfxScrollFrame.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "74cd260c31d78c8e1e7e33bdfc86974288bb1344", "parents": ["fad0fd0fe971eed5eeb0f33bb96a0e7960e5c00e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1554572 - Don't apply scroll anchor adjustments if we're processing an async scroll animation. r=dholbert a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38077", "files": ["layout/generic/ScrollAnchorContainer.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "53ec0f2a6b50ca2dadaa6ee7011d0a155472d85e", "parents": ["74cd260c31d78c8e1e7e33bdfc86974288bb1344"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicolas Silva \u003cnsilva@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1565910 - Preserve batch features when merging batches. r=gw a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38080", "files": ["gfx/wr/webrender/src/batch.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f676fbe4d5e1b2bc04e369dd80bcf208930b6818", "parents": ["53ec0f2a6b50ca2dadaa6ee7011d0a155472d85e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrei Lazar \u003candrei.a.lazar@softvision.ro\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1564082 The app crash after reopening the recent closed tabs r=petru a=RyanVM\n\nThe cursor was trying to move to first record after it was closed which lead into\nIllegalStateException.\nIn order to avoid this exception, we should simply check if the cursor was already\nclosed before trying to move to the first record.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38085", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/home/CombinedHistoryAdapter.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5ae69f6246572f6014be23af60109531b915b4c6", "parents": ["f676fbe4d5e1b2bc04e369dd80bcf208930b6818"], "tags": []}], "date": 1563370011, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ccoroiu@mozilla.com"}, "11598": {"changesets": [{"author": "Tarek Ziad\u00e9 \u003ctarek@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1561404 - Ensure thread safety r=jya a=RyanVM\n\nAdds a lock in MediaCacheStream::SizeOfExcludingThis to prevent a race\ncondition with MediaCache::NoteSeek\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D36880", "files": ["dom/media/MediaCache.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "83fbec55d5b97f5ebc864b0864339c880fa8894c", "parents": ["5ae69f6246572f6014be23af60109531b915b4c6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset ec4aac5a6c9f (bug 1557771) for performance regressions a=backout", "files": ["dom/base/nsJSEnvironment.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4829e3f23d9d0db45bfbb27c7eccba31a64aa603", "parents": ["83fbec55d5b97f5ebc864b0864339c880fa8894c"], "tags": []}], "date": 1563371650, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "11599": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nhr -\u003e 09cc31597087\nhsb -\u003e 6dc856ea94b9\nit -\u003e 0c28862264f4\nnn-NO -\u003e a7fd09cfc8c3\nsv-SE -\u003e 06134b59b194\nuk -\u003e a76b78941991\nvi -\u003e 94dfd7478544\nzh-CN -\u003e d69617f19d99\nzh-TW -\u003e 118871907695", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "88a992a80d51e697b5b3997a45f4fd9ead830e8a", "parents": ["4829e3f23d9d0db45bfbb27c7eccba31a64aa603"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nhr -\u003e 09cc31597087\nhsb -\u003e 6dc856ea94b9\nit -\u003e 0c28862264f4\nnn-NO -\u003e a7fd09cfc8c3\nsv-SE -\u003e 06134b59b194\nuk -\u003e a76b78941991\nvi -\u003e 94dfd7478544\nzh-CN -\u003e d69617f19d99\nzh-TW -\u003e 118871907695", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a7793347de9e10e12678f93a449e179658f6a77a", "parents": ["88a992a80d51e697b5b3997a45f4fd9ead830e8a"], "tags": []}], "date": 1563375632, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "11600": {"changesets": [{"author": "Nicolas Silva \u003cnsilva@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1566206 - Avoid overflow when limitting the number of rasterized blobs. r=jrmuizel a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com//D38292", "files": ["gfx/wr/webrender/src/resource_cache.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7ef06750e59177cd6b396fea3cd99d0047caf2ec", "parents": ["a7793347de9e10e12678f93a449e179658f6a77a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Drew Willcoxon \u003cadw@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1563617 - Quantumbar: Set rolluponmousewheel=\"true\" so that you can scroll in pages while the popup is open. r=dao a=RyanVM\n\nWith awesomebar we got this for free because nsXULPopupManager checks the \"type\" attribute of the popup element.  If it starts with \"autocomplete\", rolluponmousewheel is effectively true [1].  We got rid of the type attribute in quantumbar since it wasn't otherwise necessary.\n\n[1] https://searchfox.org/mozilla-central/rev/07f7390618692fa4f2a674a96b9b677df3a13450/layout/xul/nsXULPopupManager.cpp#361\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com//D38136", "files": ["browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarInput.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "65d76c6f48b2c0cd895fcb2cdf4789b4b32cc88f", "parents": ["7ef06750e59177cd6b396fea3cd99d0047caf2ec"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Shal \u003cmshal@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1561474 - Define and use a sparse profile for the profile-run task; r=sheehan a=RyanVM\n\nThis was originally from bug 1528374 for Mac PGO, but that isn't able to\nland yet and it should help Windows PGO runs in the meantime.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com//D37807", "files": ["build/sparse-profiles/profile-generate"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4335c2b0fb723f4bd682d4ba4e95f03a7b77d7d8", "parents": ["65d76c6f48b2c0cd895fcb2cdf4789b4b32cc88f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Shal \u003cmshal@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1561474 - Use sparse-profile on Windows generate tasks; r=firefox-build-system-reviewers, chmanchester a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com//D37808\n\nDepends on D37807", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/generate-profile/kind.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "128eaae4deb421e72350366371168235cf9fbb4e", "parents": ["4335c2b0fb723f4bd682d4ba4e95f03a7b77d7d8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Striemer \u003cmstriemer@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1561407 - Match message-bar font with other page styles r=rpl a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com//D35848", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/aboutaddons.css", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/message-bar.css", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/message-bar.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "94331103857527ca8ed31d5d31261bd2988d4cd0", "parents": ["128eaae4deb421e7