-bump DONTBUILD\n\nbg -\u003e 8b3606eea52c", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1cc5e1b0750b17d7c932ed55bea6aa38e11d2ddd", "parents": ["2473917cb934966d8861be42ff925d2adcf448de"], "tags": []}], "date": 1564387247, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "11647": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nbg -\u003e 08fcf831cf9c\ncy -\u003e 0be75caf0845\nen-CA -\u003e 14a2b2ef517a\neo -\u003e 665a45257de5\nsl -\u003e 09bb334cdaa3\nzh-CN -\u003e 4a6e73d3c265\nzh-TW -\u003e 65582a82069d", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "62b57d5b7754c188dcead084eeb12b6acece90ce", "parents": ["1cc5e1b0750b17d7c932ed55bea6aa38e11d2ddd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nbg -\u003e 08fcf831cf9c\ncy -\u003e 0be75caf0845\nen-CA -\u003e 14a2b2ef517a\neo -\u003e 665a45257de5\nsl -\u003e 09bb334cdaa3\nzh-CN -\u003e 4a6e73d3c265\nzh-TW -\u003e 65582a82069d", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7f9aa8519cb3d15ea122d71193ca6e8edee4e585", "parents": ["62b57d5b7754c188dcead084eeb12b6acece90ce"], "tags": []}], "date": 1564401647, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "11648": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003cffxbld@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No Bug, mozilla-beta repo-update HSTS HPKP blocklist remote-settings - a=repo-update r=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D39677", "files": ["browser/app/blocklist.xml", "security/manager/ssl/StaticHPKPins.h", "security/manager/ssl/nsSTSPreloadList.inc", "services/settings/dumps/blocklists/addons.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "52c27fa696582c056a1098b5677932f6e4eb8fc6", "parents": ["7f9aa8519cb3d15ea122d71193ca6e8edee4e585"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matthew Noorenberghe \u003cmozilla@noorenberghe.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1569414 - Don't hardcode a too old history visit date in test_Chrome_history.js. r=mak, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D39606", "files": ["browser/components/migration/tests/unit/test_Chrome_history.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "52440e49ce3b5da5ca765bfd9ac154ce5d92b453", "parents": ["52c27fa696582c056a1098b5677932f6e4eb8fc6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emily Toop \u003cetoop@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1553135 - Lock `LayerViewSupport` during detach so that other methods cannot be called during this time. r=snorp, a=RyanVM\n\nThis is caused by a race condition when the compositor is detached. Because the actual detachment happens in a new thread, `detach` can complete and release the lock on `mLayerViewSupport`, and `RecvScreenPixels` can obtain the lock, before `mLayerViewSupport` is properly cleaned up. We therefore check to ensure that `lvs` is not null before calling a method on it.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D36928", "files": ["widget/android/nsWindow.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ddfa84bcad9cc67afb25167c889c6ff28eea0d78", "parents": ["52440e49ce3b5da5ca765bfd9ac154ce5d92b453"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emily Toop \u003cetoop@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1560641: Add a lock around `mCapturePixelsResults`. r=snorp, a=RyanVM\n\nThis is to ensure that multiple completions cannot be attempted on the same `GeckoResult`, resulting in crashes.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D36929", "files": ["mobile/android/geckoview/src/androidTest/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/test/ScreenshotTest.kt", "widget/android/nsWindow.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b04fe5054ebd5f4f0df4e25651e8243cfe92242b", "parents": ["ddfa84bcad9cc67afb25167c889c6ff28eea0d78"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Lee Salzman \u003clsalzman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1568858 - always stretch box shadows except for Cairo. r=jrmuizel, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D39412", "files": ["gfx/thebes/gfxBlur.cpp", "layout/reftests/box-shadow/reftest.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "383500a28e6e5b19c7177a63c2837b815768363f", "parents": ["b04fe5054ebd5f4f0df4e25651e8243cfe92242b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrea Marchesini \u003camarchesini@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1567419 - Ensure the BodyStreamHolder has a valid stream always, r=smaug, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38814", "files": ["dom/base/BodyStream.cpp", "dom/base/BodyStream.h", "dom/fetch/Fetch.cpp", "dom/fetch/Fetch.h", "dom/file/Blob.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1eee7ed3de831a92e58f0328b6c3f817ca0c4d13", "parents": ["383500a28e6e5b19c7177a63c2837b815768363f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "sotaro \u003csotaro.ikeda.g@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1568419 - Handle a case that NumSubTextures() returns 0 in AsyncImagePipelineManager::UpdateImageKeys() r=nical, a=RyanVM\n\nGPUVideoTextureHost::NumSubTextures() returns 0 when wrapped TextureHost does not exist. In this case, we do not have a content of GPUVideoTextureHost for WR render. And EnsureWrappedTextureHost() calling is added in GPUVideoTextureHost::NumSubTextures(), since GPUVideoTextureHost is not explicit about when a wrapped TextureHost is created.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D39137", "files": ["gfx/layers/composite/GPUVideoTextureHost.cpp", "gfx/layers/composite/GPUVideoTextureHost.h", "gfx/layers/composite/TextureHost.cpp", "gfx/layers/composite/TextureHost.h", "gfx/layers/d3d11/TextureD3D11.cpp", "gfx/layers/d3d11/TextureD3D11.h", "gfx/layers/opengl/MacIOSurfaceTextureHostOGL.cpp", "gfx/layers/opengl/MacIOSurfaceTextureHostOGL.h", "gfx/layers/wr/AsyncImagePipelineManager.cpp", "gfx/layers/wr/WebRenderTextureHost.cpp", "gfx/layers/wr/WebRenderTextureHost.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "03ecebbe614d362db589181059186b165265956b", "parents": ["1eee7ed3de831a92e58f0328b6c3f817ca0c4d13"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Haik Aftandilian \u003chaftandilian@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1566540 - [10.15] Crash in [@ CrashReporter::TerminateHandler]. r=spohl, a=RyanVM\n\nTo avoid crashing in macOS 10.15, allow access to the proc_info PROC_INFO_CALL_SETCONTROL syscall variant in the GMP and RDD sandboxes.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D39079", "files": ["security/sandbox/mac/SandboxPolicyGMP.h", "security/sandbox/mac/SandboxPolicyUtility.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d65aa43e6960433cc6eacb88887c3184079cd66f", "parents": ["03ecebbe614d362db589181059186b165265956b"], "tags": []}], "date": 1564410981, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "11649": {"changesets": [{"author": "Marco Bonardo \u003cmbonardo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1560228 - Strip only leading question marks from search string. r=adw a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D39206", "files": ["browser/components/urlbar/tests/UrlbarTestUtils.jsm", "browser/components/urlbar/tests/browser/browser_keyword.js", "toolkit/components/places/UnifiedComplete.jsm", "toolkit/components/places/tests/unifiedcomplete/test_restrict_searchstring.js", "toolkit/components/places/tests/unifiedcomplete/test_search_engine_alias.js", "toolkit/components/places/tests/unifiedcomplete/test_tab_matches.js", "toolkit/components/places/tests/unifiedcomplete/xpcshell.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c8e5ac81cde26c979183b839f51dedff71125e9a", "parents": ["d65aa43e6960433cc6eacb88887c3184079cd66f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicolas Chevobbe \u003cnchevobbe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1563914 - Fix ConsoleTable with invalid headers. r=Honza, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D37164", "files": ["devtools/client/webconsole/components/Output/ConsoleTable.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/test/mochitest/browser_webconsole_console_table.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "81429c99783c16e8056af18656d913a2b984b64f", "parents": ["c8e5ac81cde26c979183b839f51dedff71125e9a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kershaw Chang \u003ckershaw@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1309358 - P1: Add wildcard to Access-Control-Expose-Headers. r=baku, a=RyanVM\n\nFor requests without credentials, add wildcard to Access-Control-Expose-Headers.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D36624", "files": ["dom/fetch/FetchDriver.cpp", "dom/fetch/InternalHeaders.cpp", "dom/fetch/InternalHeaders.h", "dom/fetch/InternalResponse.cpp", "dom/fetch/InternalResponse.h", "dom/xhr/XMLHttpRequestMainThread.cpp", "testing/web-platform/meta/fetch/api/cors/cors-expose-star.sub.any.js.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "80afdf70f4a32845d41a53df0d34d9535f1769d8", "parents": ["81429c99783c16e8056af18656d913a2b984b64f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kershaw Chang \u003ckershaw@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1309358 - P2: Add wildcard to Access-Control-Allow-Method and Access-Control-Allow-Headers. r=baku,mayhemer, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D36990", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/http/nsCORSListenerProxy.cpp", "testing/web-platform/meta/fetch/api/cors/cors-preflight-star.any.js.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/service-workers/cache-storage/serviceworker/cache-match.https.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/service-workers/cache-storage/window/cache-match.https.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/service-workers/cache-storage/worker/cache-match.https.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/service-workers/service-worker/fetch-cors-exposed-header-names.https.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "82c9cdc700d8ad1f23c95d9b37c3718ecdb20479", "parents": ["80afdf70f4a32845d41a53df0d34d9535f1769d8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kershaw Chang \u003ckershaw@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1564175 - Revert the quick fix from bug 1559795. r=ckerschb, a=RyanVM\n\nAdd the length check back.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38186", "files": ["dom/base/nsContentUtils.cpp", "testing/web-platform/meta/fetch/api/headers/headers-no-cors.window.js.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5983f1230981d44c1e288d015c16829c0e02b963", "parents": ["82c9cdc700d8ad1f23c95d9b37c3718ecdb20479"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1568108 - Indent popup sub-item in the identity popup. r=pbz, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38959", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser-siteIdentity.js", "browser/themes/shared/notification-icons.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ee661cec41883f22ea0f6ae082f07c80a7131c1f", "parents": ["5983f1230981d44c1e288d015c16829c0e02b963"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1566783 - Don't prevent PresShell::ScrollToAnchor() from working due to scroll anchoring adjustments that happen without the user scrolling. r=dholbert, a=RyanVM\n\nWe were bailing out because scroll anchoring adjustments can make this check\nfail:\n\n  * https://searchfox.org/mozilla-central/rev/22b330ecb3edba1536a54887060cbdd09db21c59/layout/base/PresShell.cpp#3194\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38397", "files": ["layout/base/PresShell.h", "layout/generic/ScrollAnchorContainer.cpp", "layout/generic/test/file_SlowTallImage.sjs", "layout/generic/test/file_bug1566783.html", "layout/generic/test/mochitest.ini", "layout/generic/test/test_bug1566783.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ed74dcb0d208a1f1c880ac1f23b05b37e81ddd00", "parents": ["ee661cec41883f22ea0f6ae082f07c80a7131c1f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1566783 - Make sure to clear mLastAnchorScrolledTo after calling PresShell::ScrollToAnchor(). r=dholbert, a=RyanVM\n\nSeems we can leave this node alive for too long if the user scrolls between\ndomcontentloaded (where GoToAnchor is called) and onload (where ScrollToAnchor()\nis called).\n\nThough it seems we can leave it for too long if we don't end up calling\nScrollToAnchor(), the documentation of the method claims that it's cleared\nunconditionally.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38398", "files": ["layout/base/PresShell.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "56362f37f5bde34e664a8428a4f12271e70b932e", "parents": ["ed74dcb0d208a1f1c880ac1f23b05b37e81ddd00"], "tags": []}], "date": 1564415376, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "11650": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nbg -\u003e 8c4bf00aefde\nbr -\u003e a5c231c54d33\ncy -\u003e e707581fff58\nen-CA -\u003e f0164167a72d\nes-AR -\u003e 17f3638af8cf\nfr -\u003e d50b41557849\ngn -\u003e 9b3e1209822e\nit -\u003e d76bf2420924\nnl -\u003e 0e9304c10bcd\npt-PT -\u003e 2a8983b0fa7a\nsl -\u003e 2c9c5f2f25a1\nsv-SE -\u003e 40244cdb8224\nth -\u003e 4937e4074862\ntrs -\u003e 21aef184791f\nuk -\u003e 13e4593384b8\nzh-CN -\u003e 2c9d1112f337\nzh-TW -\u003e 6025be92430d", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f30ea3cd87e51258dc48c3cda219f4f21603710e", "parents": ["56362f37f5bde34e664a8428a4f12271e70b932e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nbg -\u003e 8c4bf00aefde\nbr -\u003e a5c231c54d33\ncy -\u003e e707581fff58\nen-CA -\u003e f0164167a72d\nes-AR -\u003e 17f3638af8cf\nfr -\u003e d50b41557849\ngn -\u003e 9b3e1209822e\nia -\u003e f04177789dad\nit -\u003e d76bf2420924\nnl -\u003e 0e9304c10bcd\npt-PT -\u003e 2a8983b0fa7a\nsl -\u003e 2c9c5f2f25a1\nsv-SE -\u003e 40244cdb8224\nth -\u003e 4937e4074862\nuk -\u003e 13e4593384b8\nzh-CN -\u003e 2c9d1112f337\nzh-TW -\u003e 6025be92430d", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e6c4bbc211b1b9588d39c92d3d470c4283e2ba09", "parents": ["f30ea3cd87e51258dc48c3cda219f4f21603710e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1564423249, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "11651": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jason Laster \u003cjlaster@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1560942 - Fix perf regression from Event listener breakpoints. r=loganfsmyth\n, a=RyanVM\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D36826", "files": ["devtools/client/debugger/flow-typed/npm-custom/devtools-wasm-dwarf_vx.x.x.js", "devtools/client/debugger/src/actions/event-listeners.js", "devtools/client/debugger/src/reducers/event-listeners.js", "devtools/client/debugger/src/utils/bootstrap.js", "devtools/client/debugger/src/utils/prefs.js", "devtools/client/preferences/debugger.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c54e8884fddbc27992b71eed84f0be7429cb26c8", "parents": ["e6c4bbc211b1b9588d39c92d3d470c4283e2ba09"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jason Laster \u003cjlaster@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1565485 - Bug 1544329 - Fix debugger schema validation. r=davidwalsh, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D37923", "files": ["devtools/client/debugger/src/utils/prefs.js", "devtools/client/debugger/test/mochitest/helpers.js", "devtools/client/preferences/debugger.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6ab95c10bcde509b6856b90c53da3c26c6d86a17", "parents": ["c54e8884fddbc27992b71eed84f0be7429cb26c8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Drew Willcoxon \u003cadw@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1502821 - Don't autofill bookmarks when browser.urlbar.suggest.bookmark is false. r=mak, a=RyanVM\n\n* Add a new case for when suggest.bookmark = false to the logic that returns the appropriate SQL query. Don't autofill bookmarks in that case.\n* Add a bunch of new tests that cover all cases\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38394", "files": ["toolkit/components/places/UnifiedComplete.jsm", "toolkit/components/places/tests/unifiedcomplete/autofill_tasks.js", "toolkit/components/places/tests/unifiedcomplete/test_autofill_origins.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9f40d7849c3a5010758acae73acdcb5e4e71b2e8", "parents": ["6ab95c10bcde509b6856b90c53da3c26c6d86a17"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Striemer \u003cmstriemer@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1547017 - Hide the more options button when there are no items. r=mixedpuppy, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38926", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/aboutaddons.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_html_detail_view.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dd6a89eaa38510e693f519c73d06a7627a1bf1ee", "parents": ["9f40d7849c3a5010758acae73acdcb5e4e71b2e8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicolas Chevobbe \u003cnchevobbe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1559717 - Fix displaying getter value for getter returning falsy values. r=davidwalsh, a=RyanVM\n\nWe were displaying result.value.throw if result.value.return\nwas falsy. But it can happen that a getter does return a\nfalsy value, and we want to display it.\nSo now we turn the expression the other way around, we first\ncheck result.value.throw, and then default to result.value.return.\nA mochitest is added to ensure we hav expected value for different\ngetters returning falsy values.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D39136", "files": ["devtools/client/debugger/packages/devtools-reps/src/object-inspector/reducer.js", "devtools/client/shared/components/reps/reps.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/test/mochitest/browser_webconsole_object_inspector_getters.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "68d805c33a72dc54e6663bcfb2ec9945ccd439cd", "parents": ["dd6a89eaa38510e693f519c73d06a7627a1bf1ee"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Cooper \u003cmcooper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1564818 pt1 - Update about:studies after pressing \"remove study\", even if the remove failed. r=Gijs, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38929", "files": ["toolkit/components/normandy/actions/BranchedAddonStudyAction.jsm", "toolkit/components/normandy/content/AboutPages.jsm", "toolkit/components/normandy/test/browser/browser_about_studies.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "73211224425a44f76bfe8d151003c64ff8d0f6c1", "parents": ["68d805c33a72dc54e6663bcfb2ec9945ccd439cd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Cooper \u003cmcooper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1564818 pt2 - Don't fail to uninstall studies if a callback throws an exception. r=Gijs, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38930", "files": ["toolkit/components/normandy/lib/AddonStudies.jsm", "toolkit/components/normandy/test/NormandyTestUtils.jsm", "toolkit/components/normandy/test/unit/test_addon_unenroll.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ae9514b369987562c68ec099a7cef11bb228a349", "parents": ["73211224425a44f76bfe8d151003c64ff8d0f6c1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gian-Carlo Pascutto \u003cgcp@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1565996 - Handle relative paths in linker config parsing. r=jld, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38634", "files": ["security/sandbox/linux/broker/SandboxBrokerPolicyFactory.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e3cc2a54770d39526562d09a5cb3ddd34fc878b6", "parents": ["ae9514b369987562c68ec099a7cef11bb228a349"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jeff Muizelaar \u003cjrmuizel@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1565980. Force wmode 'gpu' to 'direct'. r=jmathies, a=RyanVM\n\nThis fixes wmode='gpu' with WebRender.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D39420", "files": ["dom/plugins/ipc/PluginModuleParent.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "70b4a4703c5f4494c03250b938b619571418f144", "parents": ["e3cc2a54770d39526562d09a5cb3ddd34fc878b6"], "tags": []}], "date": 1564423517, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "11652": {"changesets": [{"author": "Alvina Waseem \u003cawaseem@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1557096 - Add ContentDelegate.onKill() to differentiate between content process crashes and kills. r=agi,snorp, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D39732", "files": ["mobile/android/geckoview/api.txt", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/androidTest/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/test/ContentDelegateTest.kt", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/androidTest/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/test/rule/GeckoSessionTestRule.java", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/androidTest/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/test/util/RuntimeCreator.java", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/GeckoRuntime.java", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/GeckoSession.java", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/doc-files/CHANGELOG.md", "mobile/android/modules/geckoview/ContentCrashHandler.jsm", "mobile/android/modules/geckoview/GeckoViewContent.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2d4a2ec991541f772e9a26863ee5132221e95d81", "parents": ["70b4a4703c5f4494c03250b938b619571418f144"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Aaron Klotz \u003caklotz@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1567614: Part 1 - Refactor launcher process's LaunchUnelevated to delegate to ShellExecuteByExplorer; r=jmathies, a=RyanVM\n\nThis is just so that both the launcher process and other Gecko code can share\nthis method.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38943", "files": ["browser/app/winlauncher/LaunchUnelevated.cpp", "widget/windows/ShellHeaderOnlyUtils.h", "widget/windows/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "eb91f1f3358e0b044518aa08e7e0388ec1e49a7c", "parents": ["2d4a2ec991541f772e9a26863ee5132221e95d81"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Aaron Klotz \u003caklotz@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1567614: Part 2 - Add ShellExecuteByExplorer overload to handle absolute PIDL lists; r=jmathies, a=RyanVM\n\nFor the URI handling case, we still want to parse the URI to look for any\nmalformation. OTOH, IShellDispatch2::ShellExecute does not accept PIDLs as\narguments, we we need an overload that converts the absolute PIDL back to a\npath for the purposes of passing on to that interface.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38944", "files": ["widget/windows/ShellHeaderOnlyUtils.h", "widget/windows/WinHeaderOnlyUtils.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "daeca9ef3140434cc02f06a824b816128a0641eb", "parents": ["eb91f1f3358e0b044518aa08e7e0388ec1e49a7c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Aaron Klotz \u003caklotz@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1567614: Part 3 - Use ShellExecuteByExplorer in nsMIMEInfoWin; r=jmathies, a=RyanVM\n\nNow that we have built up the required primatives in previous patches, this\npatch simply replaces the previous code with a new version that uses the new\nAPIs from ShellHeaderOnlyUtils.h.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38945", "files": ["uriloader/exthandler/win/nsMIMEInfoWin.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "23d9c50ee55a5c0b99359a5218f648c0e4ac8198", "parents": ["daeca9ef3140434cc02f06a824b816128a0641eb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Barret Rennie \u003cbarret@brennie.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1562821 - Propagate nsIWebProgress events to the \u003cxul:browser\u003e in responsive design mode. r=Ehsan, a=RyanVM\n\nThe work from bug 1510569 that has ported the majority of the `nsIWebProgress`\nevent handlers from `WebProgressChild`/`RemoteWebProgress` to\n`BrowserChild`/`BrowserParent` was not properly propogating the events in the\nresponsive design mode case. The `BrowserParent` assumed that its frame element\nwas an `nsIBrowser`, but in RDM it is an `\u003ciframe mozbrowser\u003e` which does not\nimplement `nsIBrowser`. In the RDM case we now walk up the document in the\n`BrowserParent` tree to find the `\u003cxul:browser\u003e` and call the event handlers on\nthat instead.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38916", "files": ["dom/ipc/BrowserParent.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "146120adc5c87fa572b9a4474346f8690d01891a", "parents": ["23d9c50ee55a5c0b99359a5218f648c0e4ac8198"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Barret Rennie \u003cbarret@brennie.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1562821 - Gracefully handle loading browser-child.js in the parent. r=Ehsan, a=RyanVM\n\nWhen in responsive design mode, the `browser-child.js` script will be loaded by\nthe `\u003cxul:browser\u003e` in the parent process, where a `BrowserChild` does not\nexist. Attempting to retrieve this from the `DocShell` will cause an error,\npreventing the script from executing correctly. We now gracefully handle the\ncase where browser-child.js is loaded in the parent and no `BrowserChild`\nexists.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38917", "files": ["toolkit/content/browser-child.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7374e601e0b6624451c0bec4c64a036aaddbba11", "parents": ["146120adc5c87fa572b9a4474346f8690d01891a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Barret Rennie \u003cbarret@brennie.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1562821 - Mirror state from the \u003cxul:browser\u003e to the \u003ciframe mozbrowser\u003e when in RDM. r=ochameau, a=RyanVM\n\nAs part of bug 1510569, the majority of the `nsIWebProgress` event listeners\nhave moved from the `WebProgressChild`/`RemoteWebProgress` to the\n`BrowserChild`/`BrowserParent`. In responsive design mode, the\n`RemoteWebProgress` previously would update the state of the `\u003ciframe\nmozbrowser\u003e` with document URI and title which would be mirrored back to the\n`\u003cxul:browser\u003e` when leaving RDM. However, the event handlers in the\n`BrowserParent` call directly into the `\u003cxul:browser\u003e`, skipping the `\u003ciframe\nmozbrowser\u003e` entirely. Therefore, when RDM is shut down, old state will be\nmirroed to the `\u003cxul:browser\u003e`, leaving it in an inconsistent state. We now\nmirror the state from the `\u003cxul:browser\u003e` to the `\u003ciframe mozbrowser\u003e` with an\n`nsIWebProgressListener` so that the `\u003ciframe mozbrowser\u003e` will not clobber the\n`\u003cxul:browser\u003e`'s state when leaving RDM.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38918", "files": ["devtools/client/responsive.html/browser/tunnel.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "35e41c495b3cf7e7720d1eb41d87587ccf5b42ef", "parents": ["7374e601e0b6624451c0bec4c64a036aaddbba11"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Barret Rennie \u003cbarret@brennie.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1562821 - Mirror RemoteWebNavigation state from the \u003cxul:browser\u003e to the \u003ciframe mozbrowser\u003e when in RDM. r=ochameau, a=RyanVM\n\nIn the last patch of this series, I forgot to sync `remoteWebNavigationImpl`\nstate in the progress listener. This patch corrects that.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D39395", "files": ["devtools/client/responsive.html/browser/tunnel.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b94ef678a4be6cf724bbe4e2a33c1af8e264e811", "parents": ["35e41c495b3cf7e7720d1eb41d87587ccf5b42ef"], "tags": []}], "date": 1564426404, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "11653": {"changesets": [{"author": "Lee Salzman \u003clsalzman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1565158 - Allow forcing DWrite symmetric rendering mode. r=jrmuizel, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D38569", "files": ["gfx/2d/2D.h", "gfx/2d/Factory.cpp", "gfx/2d/ScaledFontDWrite.cpp", "gfx/2d/ScaledFontDWrite.h", "gfx/skia/skia/include/ports/SkTypeface_win.h", "gfx/skia/skia/src/ports/SkFontHost_win.cpp", "gfx/skia/skia/src/ports/SkScalerContext_win_dw.cpp", "gfx/skia/skia/src/ports/SkTypeface_win_dw.h", "gfx/thebes/gfxDWriteFonts.cpp", "gfx/wr/webrender/src/platform/windows/font.rs", "gfx/wr/webrender_api/src/font.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dd328d8b3a0ff4079a5aff7d4996725d96ffe17d", "parents": ["b94ef678a4be6cf724bbe4e2a33c1af8e264e811"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Lee Salzman \u003clsalzman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1553818 - use GDI ClearType contrast for GDI font gamma. r=jrmuizel, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D39101", "files": ["gfx/skia/skia/src/ports/SkTypeface_win_dw.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxDWriteFonts.cpp", "gfx/wr/webrender/src/platform/windows/font.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a5573dc631138b3a3d4415bb3c6b500a9a65eab0", "parents": ["dd328d8b3a0ff4079a5aff7d4996725d96ffe17d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Lee Salzman \u003clsalzman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1568841 - Don't use enhanced contrast on GDI fonts. r=jfkthame, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D39366", "files": ["gfx/thebes/gfxDWriteFonts.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4859fe78b41602342cb67bd6409f1ed79c8030db", "parents": ["a5573dc631138b3a3d4415bb3c6b500a9a65eab0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Lee Salzman \u003clsalzman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1568841 - force GDI parameters for GDI render mode. r=jrmuizel, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D39529", "files": ["gfx/thebes/gfxDWriteFonts.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dcfb654ea440ff77d19f3243f7ce0a40c1650cf1", "parents": ["4859fe78b41602342cb67bd6409f1ed79c8030db"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 2d4a2ec99154 (bug 1557096) for Android apilint bustage.", "files": ["mobile/android/geckoview/api.txt", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/androidTest/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/test/ContentDelegateTest.kt", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/androidTest/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/test/rule/GeckoSessionTestRule.java", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/androidTest/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/test/util/RuntimeCreator.java", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/GeckoRuntime.java", "mobile/android/gec