7bad8525b", "parents": ["605fe408fac1e1c8613c860118c9a0b999ddf0b4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jeff Gilbert \u003cjgilbert@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1562462 - ANGLE Cherry-pick: Fix occasional corruption of vertex textures in HD4600 GPUs for WebRender. r=gw a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D40354", "files": ["gfx/angle/checkout/out/gen/angle/id/commit.h", "gfx/angle/checkout/src/libANGLE/renderer/d3d/d3d11/renderer11_utils.cpp", "gfx/angle/cherry_picks.txt"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "af67ed2165eb1b23c6dc1a9485dbd68a11985484", "parents": ["1cb600dceac23344e33eb9d970ffd5a7bad8525b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Botond Ballo \u003cbotond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1568826 - Restrict the fix for bug 1549625 to cases where we have a zoomable viewport. r=tnikkel a=pascalc\n\nThe fix for bug 1549625 is only necessary in cases where the layout and\nvisual viewports can diverge (currently mobile, and later desktop zooming),\nbut it has caused regressions in desktop scenarios that don't involve zooming.\n\nWhile we can get a proper fix in place (tracked in bug 1543485), restricting\nthe existing fix to zoomable configurations mitigates the regressions.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D40473", "files": ["layout/generic/nsGfxScrollFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8787ce24bafe9bf68892910dd842dc79b1323ef6", "parents": ["af67ed2165eb1b23c6dc1a9485dbd68a11985484"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bob Owen \u003cbobowencode@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1565932: Add more Printer dialog completion messages to be reposted on x86 Windows. r=jmathies a=pascalc\n\nThese are now being hit because of the removal of the HTML frames\ncustomizations to the print dialog.\nI've removed the defines for these, because I don't think there is any point\ntrying to guess what their uses are.\nI've also made it 32-bit only, because we only see them on 32-bit Windows 7.\nIn fact only 32-bit Firefox on 64-bit Windows 7 I believe.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D40433", "files": ["widget/windows/nsAppShell.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cc946a12662c46a953e299e7ac1ff6ddff573a0f", "parents": ["8787ce24bafe9bf68892910dd842dc79b1323ef6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Drew Willcoxon \u003cadw@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1570492 - Make browser.topSites.get({ newtab: true }) prefer sites' labels to titles. r=mixedpuppy a=pascalc\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D40112", "files": ["browser/components/extensions/parent/ext-topSites.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "440c7ba936c5a5344ecd5be2801f1e8da229d361", "parents": ["cc946a12662c46a953e299e7ac1ff6ddff573a0f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1565209126, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "shindli@mozilla.com"}, "11734": {"changesets": [{"author": "Sebastian Hengst \u003carchaeopteryx@coole-files.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 1739cecb82b2 (bug 1565273) for landing without proper commit message. a=backout", "files": ["browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarInput.jsm", "browser/components/urlbar/tests/browser/browser.ini", "browser/components/urlbar/tests/browser/browser_urlbar_selection.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "31cd2ca2e2d9104636a3ca070ac82bc6edddbd79", "parents": ["440c7ba936c5a5344ecd5be2801f1e8da229d361"], "tags": []}, {"author": "harry \u003chtwyford@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1565273 - Context menu clicks ignore browser.urlbar.clickSelectsAll pref. Add tests for selectAll behaviour. r=mak a=pascalc", "files": ["browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarInput.jsm", "browser/components/urlbar/tests/browser/browser.ini", "browser/components/urlbar/tests/browser/browser_urlbar_sel