3e 75e814c96a9a\nuk -\u003e 791fc4c3f2b1\nvi -\u003e 114b586bdf1c\nzh-CN -\u003e 625456488a93", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "96344a15e6b69f7a8a0363d4cd96633cbbd4c07a", "parents": ["8c9a846451012c047a342024fd636cc963861518"], "tags": []}], "date": 1566208844, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "11809": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003cffxbld@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No Bug, mozilla-beta repo-update HSTS HPKP remote-settings - a=repo-update r=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D42501", "files": ["security/manager/ssl/StaticHPKPins.h", "security/manager/ssl/nsSTSPreloadList.inc"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4b32122fde5655c660315c74102a043f57e9ad62", "parents": ["96344a15e6b69f7a8a0363d4cd96633cbbd4c07a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1568397 part 1 - Fix definite properties analysis to use the correct group for constraints. r=iain,tcampbell, r=RyanVM\n\nWe now add information about the constraints to a new class (DPAConstraintInfo)\nso we can then finish all constraints at the end. This is also nice to avoid\nadding unnecessary constraints when the analysis fails.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D40444", "files": ["js/src/jit/IonAnalysis.cpp", "js/src/jit/IonAnalysis.h", "js/src/vm/TypeInference.cpp", "js/src/vm/TypeInference.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fd21aed8462aa60060c20059286044a846b2bbe1", "parents": ["4b32122fde5655c660315c74102a043f57e9ad62"], "tags": []}, {"author": "John Lin \u003cjolin@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1565838 - don't check timestamp of EOS samples. r=jya, a=RyanVM\n\nBug 1540748/D28167 checks the output sample timestamp against the\ntime parsed by demuxer to determine the validness. However, unlike\nAndroid builtin MP3 decoder which sets EOS flag in the final valid\noutput, the Samsung MP3 decoder always emit additional EOS sample\nwith invalid timestamp. To address this, the timestamp check should\nbe ignore for EOS samples.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D41872", "files": ["dom/media/platforms/android/RemoteDataDecoder.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ae6de9d94b5f9ed242dbb4418438fd8871a23851", "parents": ["fd21aed8462aa60060c20059286044a846b2bbe1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrea Marchesini \u003camarchesini@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1541344 - Delete plugin-data only for the sites with data. r=gsvelto, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D40644", "files": ["toolkit/components/cleardata/ClearDataService.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "26469ee275619eb3ee13dc37aae505d2de68d89d", "parents": ["ae6de9d94b5f9ed242dbb4418438fd8871a23851"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Drew Willcoxon \u003cadw@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1571161 - Modify openViewOnFocus so that it doesn't open the view on the newtab page and in private windows. r=dao, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D40719", "files": ["browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarInput.jsm", "browser/components/urlbar/tests/browser/browser.ini", "browser/components/urlbar/tests/browser/browser_openViewOnFocus.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d047e1dbad3b2f30eab8154c76150e0f7e18c580", "parents": ["26469ee275619eb3ee13dc37aae505d2de68d89d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1571682 - Make allocationSiteGroup fail cleanly on OOM. r=tcampbell,jandem, a=RyanVM\n\nThis should make this fail cleanly on OOM rather than crashing, which should make this crash go away (without reducing memory usage obviously). The problem was the lack of hasHash/ensureHash methods that we use to handle OOM when generating unique IDs for GC things. I also tidied the equivalent code for ObjectGroupRealm::NewEntry (FallibleHashMethods is already implemented for MovableCellHasher).\n\nWe could further improve this by giving each script an immutable hash code on creation if you think it's worth the tradeoff of storing this for every script.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D41233", "files": ["js/src/vm/ObjectGroup.cpp", "js/src/vm/ObjectGroup.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e1341fad0145dddfa2056caad74136b73b89e163", "parents": ["d047e1dbad3b2f30eab8154c76150e0f7e18c580"], "tags": []}], "date": 1566227462, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "11810": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nbn -\u003e 40d6251ecd11\nel -\u003e cc321f230c6d\neo -\u003e 0753f929569f\neu -\u003e 9c39203cd09a\nfi -\u003e e4ef807514b0\nhu -\u003e 86df8c7ee773\nit -\u003e 8871e62e052f\nja -\u003e d9c77544551a\nka -\u003e 0a24d1e18a3e\nnn-NO -\u003e e163b774d86d\npa-IN -\u003e a15215a07313\nro -\u003e 1f02dfb8dad6\nsl -\u003e 0b24111ba6fc\nth -\u003e 16198c0ffcc2\nuk -\u003e d4333d08184d\nzh-CN -\u003e cc3455163324", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4c1107c95830b5f1714cd408c261c015af099596", "parents": ["e1341fad0145dddfa2056caad74136b73b89e163"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nbn -\u003e 40d6251ecd11\nel -\u003e cc321f230c6d\neo -\u003e 0753f929569f\neu -\u003e 9c39203cd09a\nfi -\u003e e4ef807514b0\nhu -\u003e 86df8c7ee773\nit -\u003e 8871e62e052f\nja -\u003e d9c